				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Bard help <a name="48916"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 29 04 4:08 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes, read the guides. Please, people put a lot of time &amp; energy into them and they're there for you, for free. 
<br />

<br />
But some (more-or-less) brief answers:
<br />

<br />
1) CHA is important for missed notes, and if you're pulling sub-63, it's important for stopping critical lull failures. Post-63... well, you might want it to stop critical lull failures anyway, but it becomes less important once you get Fading Memories. I <i>think,</i> but I'm not sure, that fizzle checks are against the highest of either CHA or DEX, so if your CHA is high you don't need to worry about your DEX as much. However, I haven't confirmed that with cold hard data, and somebody might contradict me.
<br />

<br />
2) Yes. If it is an instrument-based song (rather than singing) you must equip the appropriate instrument. If it is an area effect song like fear or AE damage, please don't do it in populated areas, it annoys people and gives bards a bad reputation.
<br />

<br />
3) Nobody. Of course, I'm biased. I'm a Vah Shir, Agnostic is the only option we get, and I like it that way. Anyway, going Agnostic means you can use illusion masks to sneak into places that would normally be KOS to you if you worshipped the wrong god. The drawback is that you can't use cultural armors or some idols. Honestly, I've never looked at an idol and said to myself, &quot;Gee, that would be so much better than a Grandmaster's Trophy in my range slot, I simply must reroll as a half elf and worship Tunare!&quot;
<br />

<br />
4) Yes.
<br />
At low levels, your melee damage is on a par with other hybrids and your songs aren't THAT powerful yet, so definitely get in there and tank. However, even if you're going to tank, turn off your songs as mobs are incoming - that initial group buff is often enough to grab agro and get you whupped.
<br />
At mid levels other hybrids start outdamaging you. At that point, it doesn't hurt to melee a lot of the time. However there might be situations such as when you're pulling and you need somebody else to get agro off of you, or when you're mezzing and you don't want to accidentally autoattack the mob you just targetted and mezzed, when you're going to want to turn attack off and focus on songs.
<br />
Then as you level higher and higher your damage starts to really suck compared to all the other &quot;melee&quot; classes and you end up taking far more damage in ripostes than you're dealing in melee, and your pitiful melee damage is crap compared to how much you could help your group by equipping your instrument, so you (hopefully) realize that it makes more sense to hang back and focus on songs.
<br />

<br />
As the Reading Rainbow guy says: &quot;Don't take my word for it!&quot; Read the guides.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
