				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Bard help <a name="48992"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 29 04 11:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I put all my stats into Dex and charisma. I am level 65 with 340 AA, and I have never regretted that decision. Strength and stamina are easier to max than Char and Dex imho. I have found AGI a tough stat to max too without sacrificing other stats.
<br />

<br />
Tank or not? The answer is both. It depends on the situation, but at higher levels you aren't an efficient tank.
<br />

<br />
Religion:  Doesn't matter at higher levels. If you want high HP gear you can go RZ and get the cultural armor. However, that armor is missing so much of what a bard needs that it is really not a reason to pick a religion other than maybe for the 40 to 55 levels.
<br />

<br />
Skill ups: yes singing a song all day will get you skill ups. Just don't do an AE song near other people.
<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
65 Bard
<br />
Torv Server</span></td>
